Text.Value: |You should know that your life is insignifacnt. Dying for your Queen is an honor!|
|Farewell.|
|I will not hand over the artefact.|
|Using Orpheus's power to our advantage is our best chance against the illithids.|
|Kill them!|
|Now. Hand over the artefact.|
|That is foolish. We can deal with both threats at once.|
|Yet, the one inside is still alive. Why haven't you acted on it yet?|
|Do you doubt your Queen?|
|It was an honor serving my Queen.|
|I am quite interested in seeing what you can do with it.|
|How lovely! You did a great job disposing of this traitor.|
|Interesting take. Alright.|
|I couldn't do it. It's the only thing protecting me now.|
|I've heard enough. Guards - take the artefact and kill her.|
|How amusing. Just after you fought a dragon, you think you can stop me from taking it?|
|For this, you will pay with your life. And the artefact.|
|Now, hand it over.|
|Now, we have time to talk. Tell me, why have you been avoiding your duties?|
|I have tried! I went to the Creche!
|How lovely! You did a great job disposing of this traitor.|
|Listen, Orpheus can help against the illithi-|
|How unfortunate that your companion had to suffer through this.|
|You have what Vlaakith is seeking.|
|I wish I could, but it's the only thing protecting me.|
|I will let you keep it for now, but will keep a close watch over your actions.|
